title: Issue #4 and #54: register for and import GPX and KML.
message:
Issue #4 and #54: register for and import GPX and KML.

A bit of a hack, but this more or less follows the iOS model.  An abstract Telemetry base class, with two subclasses (GPXReader and KMLReader) that can read GPX and KML, respectively.

The hacky bits come from the fact that MFBMain has to respond to the incoming import request, including requesting read permissions.  Also because autototals is baked into ActNewFlight, I had to (slightly) re-invent auto-fill of cross-country and auto-fill of totals.

This does NOT handle all of the many flavors of KML.  KML without timestamps is useless and ignored.  Even KML with timestamps requires speed to be derived.

Still need to move export into these classes (despite saying "reader")

Fixed a few things, including:
 - Using the passed loc for takeoff/landing, rather than the current loc
 - LocSample had no getLocation method to return a Location object.
 - MFBLocation now has a flag to suppress recording, so that we don't overwrite an in-progress flight's telemetry with imported telemetry.  (We attach the raw imported telemetry afterwards)

MFBMain has two new methods:

title: Eclipse is finally broken to where I can't figure out how to recover it; I…
message:
Eclipse is finally broken to where I can't figure out how to recover it; I deleted some SDK component or another and it won't build, so I bit the bullet and migrated to Android Studio, which, of course, rearranges everything.

 But...I'll also start this fresh in GitHub and make my first foray into open-source code.

 Code changes made (I hope I'm not missing any):
  - (Obvious) Android Studio rearrangement
  - GPL LIcense notification in each file and license at route
  - Had to edit ActFlightMap to use getMapAsync, since the code has changed
  - Removed obsolete Geopoint
  - Moved GoogleMaps key and webservice key into apikeys.xml, which is ignored.
  - Had to move to multi-dex to be able to create an APK file
  - Had to change several layouts to better include decimaledit.
